There are many columns with Unknown. For some columns number of unknown is higher than the other values count.¶

  1. Drop the columns where frequent is Unknown
  2. Impute the Unknown with frequent(mode) of the column
In [10]:
# drop the poutcome column
dataset = dataset.drop(["poutcome"] , axis=1)

#replace Unknown with mode
dataset["contact"].replace(to_replace = ['unknown'] , value =dataset["contact"].mode() , inplace = True)
dataset["education"].replace(to_replace =['unknown'] , value =dataset["education"].mode() , inplace = True)
dataset["job"].replace(to_replace = ['unknown'] , value =dataset["job"].mode() , inplace = True)

In [12]:

dataset.shape
Out[12]:

In [13]:
num_cols = dataset.describe().columns
Q1 = dataset[num_cols].quantile(0.05) # calculate the first quantile
Q3 = dataset[num_cols].quantile(0.95) # calculate the third quantile
IQR = Q3 - Q1 # interquartile range
dataset = dataset[~((dataset[num_cols] < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) |(dataset[num_cols] > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))).any(axis=1)]

from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

cat_cols = dataset.describe(include = [np.object]).columns

encoders = []

for col in cat_cols:
    lbl = LabelEncoder()
    dataset.loc[:,col] = lbl.fit_transform(dataset[col])
    encoders.append(lbl)

Modelling¶

In [22]:
model_result = []

def model_function(model,name, X_train, y_train , X_test , y_test):
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    pred = model.predict(X_test)
    
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, pred )
    ac = accuracy_score(y_test, pred )
    prec = precision_score(y_test, pred )
    rec = recall_score(y_test, pred )
    
    print ("F1 Score test score : ",f1)
    print ("Accuracy test score : ",ac)
    print ("Precision test score : ",prec)
    print ("Recall test score : ",rec)
    print ("Confusion Matrix : ")
    print (confusion_matrix(y_test, pred))
    
    print ()
    
    model_result.append(pd.DataFrame({ 
                        "Model" : [name] ,
                        "Test Accuracy" : ac,
                        "Test F1" : f1,
                        "Test Precision" :prec  , 
                        "Test Recall" : rec
                        }))
